parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering fails to assist
making it hard to turn the wheel
especially at low speeds; the vehicle makes a whining or grinding noise when turning; the power steering fluid leaks; the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Traction Control and Stabilitrak System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control and Stabilitrak system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The traction control light and Stabilitrak light come on; the vehicle loses power and acceleration; the vehicle becomes difficult to steer; the brakes malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the transmission slips gears; the vehicle loses power and acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to seize, resulting in loss of power, stalling, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine rattles or makes a loud noise
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" or have reduced acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pressure system can cause the engine to seize, resulting in loss of power, stalling, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil pressure warning light illuminates
the engine noise increases
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the oil level may be low or empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause loss of power, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving on a busy highway.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" or have reduced acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning system leaks refrigerant
the compressor fails
or the system does not cool properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak system can cause loss of traction, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving on slippery roads.
symptoms: The Stabilitrak warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses traction
or the system does not engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle loses power or hesitates when accelerating
the timing chain stretches or breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control and stability systems can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The traction control and stability systems malfunction
the vehicle loses control or stability
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle stalls or hesitates when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction of engine power can cause the vehicle to lose speed or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine power is reduced
the vehicle loses speed or stalls
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control or crash, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes malfunction
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to unexpected deployments or failures to deploy, which can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light is on
the airbag warning light illuminates
the service airbag message appears on the dashboard
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag fails to deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Connector or Wiring Harness Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag connector or wiring harness can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unexpected deployments or failures to deploy, which can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light is on
the airbag warning light illuminates
the service airbag message appears on the dashboard
the airbag connector comes apart
the wiring harness is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt locks up
the seatbelt will not release
the seatbelt wraps around the occupant's neck
the passenger airbag light comes on.
